Tourism is one of the sectors in South Africa drowning from the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic. The losses have been staggering. But now there's glimmers of hope. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It's all about revival for the South African Tourism Agency as it aims to restore the sector battling the setbacks of the coronavirus pandemic. The agency is engaging key stakeholders on ways to get more visitors on our shores and will host its African counterparts later this month. READ: Tourism industry calls for end to PCR testing for vaxxed tourists To tempt travellers, SA tourism will also shoot its first global advert since 2017 as it steps into a brave new world. Several international big-budget film and documentaries are currently being filmed in the country and domestic travel is booming.